                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                <head>3. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station</gloss> in [<hi rend="italic"
                        >place not declassified</hi>]<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d3fn1"
                        >Source: Central Intelligence Agency, Job 79–01025A, Box 7, Folder 1.
                        Secret; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1952-01-22T23:22:00+00:00">January 22, 1952, 2322Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>23889. Re: TLB-1589.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>It is requested that JULEP locate but not contact <persName
                            corresp="#p_CACC1">Carlos Castillo Armas</persName> if in Salvador or
                        Honduras. If located, headquarters should be continually advised of major
                        movements. Reference gives reported permanent [<hi rend="italic">less than 1
                            line of source text not declassified</hi>] address in Honduras.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Authorization given for JULEP travel Honduras during investigation.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
